This DEMO disk contains some GameStudio samples. Graphics and sounds
are for demonstration purposes only - they are NOT royalty free and
may not be included in games! The WDL files, however, are free:

VRDEMO.WDL   Demo source code

MOVE.WDL     Samples for different movement actions

DEBUG.WDL    Panel with numeric displays

ADJUST.WDL	 A panel to adjust the positions
             of wall and region textures

MENU.WDL     WDL actions to define a menu

INFO.WDL     WDL for debugging of actors.

MOUSE.WDL    WDL to move the mouse.

To start, open a DOS window, then start either the editor through
the DOS command WED VRDEMO -VESA, or the level directly through WED
-RUN VRDEMO. Command line option -D SVGA starts in high resolution.
By command line option -D DEBUG a panel with some indicators will
appear.

If you click the right mouse button, a mouse cursor will appear, and
all movements will 'freeze'. If you now click left onto any object,
you'll see its parameters printed onto the screen. You can now
examine his status even if you click right again, resuming the game
movements.

Hint: Should the editor display appear distorted, start WED using
the options -VGA or -VESA (see manual).

Enjoy!

